 SUMMARY {
  coords 3821.125 7.596 1805.825
  m_sTitle "Welcome"
  m_sTextData "Welcome to the Proving Grounds, Soldier!"\
  ""\
  "OVERVIEW:"\
  "This sandbox scenario provides a controlled environment to test, experiment with, and familiarize yourself with nearly all content included in our modpack. The Proving Grounds are designed to help you build confidence and proficiency with weapons, vehicles, systems, and gameplay mechanics before deploying into live operations."\
  ""\
  "RULES:"\
  "This is an open sandbox environment where combat is permitted; however, mutual respect towards others is expected."\
  "Be mindful of other players and their activities. If you observe someone clearly training, testing equipment, practicing vehicle operations, or running drills, allow them the space to do so without interference."\
  ""\
  "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION:"\
  "Briefing tabs remain accessible throughout the scenario and contain reference material commonly used during our missions. Make use of these resources to enhance your understanding and effectiveness within the Proving Grounds."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
 }
 Radios {
  coords 3803.904 0 1851.775
  m_sTitle "Radios and VP"
  m_sTextData "We define radios at here as \"Long range\" and \"Short range\" radios."\
  "Typically short range radios are used for smaller formation such as squads, while the long range radios are used for platoon, company, air, or even an artillery net."\
  "Some of these radios are single or dual role meaning they can have either one or two seperate channels to monitor at the same time."\
  ""\
  "|Voice procedures|"\
  "THINK. PUSH. SPEAK."\
  ""\
  "\"Roger\" = Ok/Yes"\
  "\"Negative\" = No/Can't do"\
  "\"Over\" = I've finished talking and awaiting a response."\
  "\"Out\" = I've finised talking and don't need a response."\
  "\"Say again\" = Repeat what you just said."\
  "\"Radio check\" = Hello can anyone hear me?"\
  "\"Sighting\" = An element or yourself has spotted something."\
  "\"Contact!\" = Used to alert others of enemy engaging friendly forces."\
  ""
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 Maps {
  coords 3808.913 0 1906.097
  m_sTitle "Map & Compass"
  m_sTextData "Map:"\
  "|GRIDS|"\
  "When getting a GRID, you move either left or right along the top or bottom first, before going either up or down on the left or right of your screen."\
  "Bottom/top are known as \"Eastings\""\
  "Left/right are known as \"Northings\""\
  ""\
  "4 digit grid = 1000m accuracy"\
  "6 digit grid = 100m accuracy"\
  "8 digit grid = 10m accuracy"\
  "10 digit grid = 1m accuracy"\
  "Grid scale is show in the bottom left corner."\
  ""\
  "|CONTOUR LINES|"\
  "Contour lines are the little black lines that go around a hill's slope for example."\
  "Your level of zoom on the map will show more or less of these and your map legend will indicate the amount of altitude change per contour line. If my map legends says 5m per contour and I see 5 contours between point A to B, then his means it's either 25m+/25m- altitude depending if I'm going up or down."\
  "A quick indication of a very steep slope or a cliff are many contour closer togeather, while further apart contours in a rolling fashion means more flat ground."\
  ""\
  "Compass:"\
  "|DEGREES AND MILS|"\
  "The inner ring on a compass are your degrees and the outer ring are Mils."\
  "Typically you'll use degrees as infantry or armour, while most likely use mils if you were an air asset or artillery due to it's better use over long distances and accuracy."\
  "Degrees ranges from 0-360, while mils ranges from 0-6400 and goes up in increments of 20, compared to increments of 1 with degrees."\
  ""\
  "|DIRECTIONS|"\
  "Cardinal directions are your North, South, East, and West."\
  "You then have intercardinal which are NE, SE, SW, NW."\
  "and finally your sub-cardinal directions which are NNE, ENE, ESE, SSE, SSW, WSW, WNW. NNW."\
  "Each one allows a user to break down their compass and be more refined in directions, without having to pull out their whole compass and get accurate bearings."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 2
 }
